<div class="policy-page">
  <div class="policy-hero">
    <div class="policy-hero-inner">
      <h1 class="policy-hero-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="policy-meta">Last Updated: May 3, 2026 &middot; Applies to: Canada and the United States</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-body container">

    <div class="policy-summary">
      <h2 class="policy-summary__title">The Short Version</h2>
      <p>Here's what you need to know about how ChairHop handles your information:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>We collect what we need to run the Platform — nothing more.</li>
        <li>We don't sell your data. Ever.</li>
        <li>We don't run ads or share your data with ad networks.</li>
        <li>Your payment details are handled by Square, not stored by us.</li>
        <li>You can ask us to access, correct, or delete your data at any time.</li>
        <li>We take security seriously and use industry-standard protections.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>The full details are below. If you have questions, email <a href="mailto:admin@chair-hop.com">admin@chair-hop.com</a>.</p>
    </div>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
      <p>ChairHop Inc. ("ChairHop," "we," "us," or "our") is based in Montreal, Quebec, Canada. We operate the ChairHop platform, which connects clients with independent hair and beauty professionals.</p>
      <p>This Privacy Policy covers how we handle personal information collected through our website, app, and any related services (collectively, the "Platform"). It applies to both clients and stylists.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>2. What We Collect and Why</h2>

      <h3>When you create an account</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Your name, email address, phone number, and password — so we can create and secure your account.</li>
        <li>Your profile photo (optional) — to personalize your profile.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>When you book or manage appointments</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Appointment details, service preferences, and booking history — to make bookings work.</li>
        <li>Messages you send through the Platform — to facilitate communication between clients and stylists.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>When you make a payment</h3>
      <p>Payment details are handled by Square. We only see limited transaction info like the last four digits of your card and the amount charged. We never store your full card number.</p>

      <h3>If you're a stylist</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Business name and address, professional credentials, service listings, portfolio photos, and availability.</li>
        <li>Banking information for payouts — stored and managed by Square, not by us.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Automatically, when you use the Platform</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Device type, browser, and operating system — for security and compatibility.</li>
        <li>IP address and approximate location — for fraud prevention.</li>
        <li>Log data like pages visited and session duration — to improve performance.</li>
        <li>Cookies and session tokens — to keep you logged in. See Section 7.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>One thing we don't collect</h3>
      <p>We don't intentionally collect sensitive information like government ID numbers, health records, or biometric data. If a client chooses to share a health condition or allergy with a stylist through the Platform, we treat that information as confidential and use it only for that appointment.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>We use your information to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Run the Platform — create accounts, facilitate bookings, process payments, send confirmations and reminders.</li>
        <li>Keep things secure — detect fraud, prevent unauthorized access, investigate suspicious activity.</li>
        <li>Improve ChairHop — understand how people use the Platform so we can make it better.</li>
        <li>Communicate with you — send transactional messages you need (like booking confirmations) and, with your permission, marketing messages about new features or offers.</li>
        <li>Comply with the law — meet our legal obligations in Canada and the US.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not use your data for advertising. We don't serve targeted ads, share your data with ad networks, or build advertising profiles.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>4. Who We Share Your Information With</h2>
      <p>We share your information only when we need to in order to run the Platform.</p>
      <table class="table policy-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Who</th>
            <th>What We Share</th>
            <th>Why</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Square Inc.</td>
            <td>Payment card data, transaction details, stylist banking info</td>
            <td>Processing payments and sending payouts to stylists</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Cloudinary</td>
            <td>Photos and media uploaded by stylists and clients</td>
            <td>Storing and delivering profile and portfolio images</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Heroku (Salesforce)</td>
            <td>App data including accounts, appointments, and logs</td>
            <td>Hosting the Platform. Servers may be in the US.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Postmark (Wildbit)</td>
            <td>Name, email, appointment details</td>
            <td>Transactional emails (confirmations, reminders, receipts) and marketing communications where consented</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>OpenAI (ChatGPT API)</td>
            <td>Text of messages sent to HOPPS</td>
            <td>Powering the HOPPS AI assistant. OpenAI's API does not use inputs to train models by default.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p>We also share information when the law requires it — for example, in response to a court order or legal process. And if ChairHop is ever acquired or merged with another company, your information may transfer as part of that deal. We'll notify you if that happens.</p>
      <p>We never sell your information, share it with advertisers, or give it to data brokers.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>5. What Clients and Stylists Share with Each Other</h2>
      <p>When you book an appointment, we share your name and contact details with the stylist so they can prepare for and manage your booking. Stylist profiles — including their name, services, photos, and availability — are visible to anyone browsing the Platform.</p>
      <p>Any messages you send through the Platform are visible to the person you're messaging. Keep that in mind when sharing sensitive information.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>6. How We Protect Your Information</h2>
      <p>We use industry-standard security measures including:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Encryption for data in transit and at rest</li>
        <li>Encrypted storage for sensitive credentials</li>
        <li>Access controls so only people who need your data can see it</li>
      </ul>
      <p>No system is 100% secure. If you think your account has been compromised, contact us at <a href="mailto:admin@chair-hop.com">admin@chair-hop.com</a> immediately.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>7. Cookies</h2>
      <p>We use cookies and session tokens to keep you logged in, remember your settings, and understand how the Platform is being used. We don't use advertising cookies or tracking pixels.</p>
      <p>You can control cookies through your browser settings. Turning them off may affect some Platform functionality.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>8. How Long We Keep Your Information</h2>
      <p>We keep your information for as long as your account is active or as long as we need it.</p>
      <table class="table policy-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Type of Data</th>
            <th>How Long We Keep It</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Account information</td>
            <td>While your account is active + 2 years after deletion</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Appointment and booking records</td>
            <td>7 years (tax and legal compliance)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Payment and transaction records</td>
            <td>7 years (tax and legal compliance)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Messages between clients and stylists</td>
            <td>While your account is active + 2 years after deletion</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>HOPPS AI conversations</td>
            <td>90 days, then deleted or anonymized</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Portfolio photos</td>
            <td>While your account is active, deleted within 30 days of account closure</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Reviews and ratings</td>
            <td>Indefinitely (anonymized if reviewer closes account)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Log and analytics data</td>
            <td>13 months, then aggregated and anonymized</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p>We may keep data longer if required by law or if there's an active legal matter.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>9. Your Privacy Rights</h2>

      <h3>Everyone</h3>
      <p>Regardless of where you live, you can:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Ask to see what personal information we have about you</li>
        <li>Ask us to correct inaccurate information</li>
        <li>Ask us to delete your information (subject to legal retention requirements)</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent for marketing communications at any time</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Canadian users (PIPEDA and Quebec's Law 25)</h3>
      <p>If you're in Canada, you also have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Request your data in a portable format (JSON or CSV) — email us with "Data Portability Request" in the subject line</li>
        <li>Ask for human review if an automated system makes a significant decision about you</li>
        <li>File a complaint with the Office of the Privacy Commissioner of Canada (<a href="https://www.priv.gc.ca" target="_blank" rel="noopener">priv.gc.ca</a>) or, if you're in Quebec, with the Commission d'accès à l'information (<a href="https://www.cai.gouv.qc.ca" target="_blank" rel="noopener">cai.gouv.qc.ca</a>)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>US users (state privacy laws)</h3>
      <p>Depending on the state you live in, you may have additional rights under state privacy laws. These may include the right to know what data we collect, the right to delete it, the right to opt out of the sale of your data (we don't sell data, but this right still applies), and the right not to be discriminated against for exercising your privacy rights.</p>
      <p>California residents: this policy serves as our notice at collection under the CCPA. We do not sell or share personal information as defined by the CCPA. You can submit a rights request by emailing <a href="mailto:admin@chair-hop.com">admin@chair-hop.com</a>.</p>

      <h3>How to submit a request</h3>
      <p>Email <a href="mailto:admin@chair-hop.com">admin@chair-hop.com</a> with "Privacy Rights Request" in the subject line. We'll respond within 30 days. We may ask you to verify your identity first.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>10. Data Outside Canada</h2>
      <p>ChairHop is based in Canada, but some of our service providers — including Square, Cloudinary, and Heroku — may store or process your data in the United States. US privacy laws are different from Canadian ones.</p>
      <p>When your data crosses the border, we protect it through contracts with our service providers that require them to keep your data safe to a standard comparable to Canadian law. We only share what's necessary for each service.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>11. HOPPS, Our AI Assistant</h2>
      <p>HOPPS is a built-in AI assistant that helps you navigate ChairHop and answers general questions. It's powered by a third-party AI provider. The text you send to HOPPS may be processed by that provider and may be used to improve their AI models, in accordance with their terms.</p>
      <p>HOPPS doesn't make any decisions about your account — it only provides information. If you want a human to review something, contact us directly at <a href="mailto:admin@chair-hop.com">admin@chair-hop.com</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>12. Children</h2>
      <p>ChairHop is not for anyone under 18. We don't knowingly collect information from minors. If you think a minor has signed up, let us know at <a href="mailto:admin@chair-hop.com">admin@chair-hop.com</a> and we'll delete the account.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>13. If There's Ever a Breach</h2>
      <p>If something goes wrong and your personal information is compromised in a way that creates real risk of harm, we'll notify you as quickly as possible. We'll also notify the appropriate regulators as required by law — the Office of the Privacy Commissioner in Canada and, for Quebec residents, the Commission d'accès à l'information.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>14. Things Outside Our Control</h2>
      <p>If a natural disaster, cyberattack, government action, or other event outside our control prevents us from handling your data the way we normally would, we'll do our best to minimize the impact and get back to normal as quickly as possible. We'll notify you if required by law.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>15. Updates to This Policy</h2>
      <p>We'll update this policy when things change — new features, new legal requirements, or new ways we use data. When we make significant changes, we'll let you know by email or by posting a notice in the app. The date at the top of this page always reflects the most recent update.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>16. Questions?</h2>
      <p>Our Privacy Officer handles all privacy-related questions and requests.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Email: <a href="mailto:admin@chair-hop.com">admin@chair-hop.com</a></li>
        <li>Mail: ChairHop Inc., Attn: Privacy Officer, Montreal, Quebec, Canada</li>
        <li>Phone: 1 (437) 333-0271</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We'll acknowledge your message within 5 business days and get back to you fully within 30 days.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="policy-back mt-5">
      <%= link_to "← Back to ChairHop", root_path %>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>
